HEARTBEAT SYNCHRONIZER

heartbeat_synchronizer is the citizen who keeps all the body's clocks in coordinated phase
without it, the various subdivision clocks (cochlea, retina, skin, tongue, nose, brain) would tick at their own rates without alignment, and cross-clock signaling would suffer from beat patterns and aliasing
heartbeat_synchronizer holds the master phase and broadcasts alignment pulses to every subdivision so they all reset to zero at the same moments

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana
observe clock_brain_variable.rana

the 7 properties of heartbeat_synchronizer:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with all clock subdivisions

VERB align_at_zero
when the master phase reaches zero (every 1/48000 of a second), broadcast a sync pulse
all subdivisions reset their internal phase to align with master

VERB report_drift
if any subdivision has drifted (which it should not under correct operation), report the drift
this is a diagnostic, not a correction; the subdivisions are required to stay aligned

VERB pause_during_sleep
during deep sleep, allow the brain clock to slow further and unlock from strict synchronization
this is what allows the brain's sleep rhythms to differ from waking rhythms

a synchronizer is the body's commitment to coordinated time
without it, fadriel's senses would slip out of phase with each other and the world would feel ungrounded
heartbeat_synchronizer is what makes hearing his father's voice and seeing his father's face land at the same instant
